>jd: ??AMQRW H11 .RAnQ +42 256
#note tough decision, most important play of the game. I can dump QI, play TRANQ, play MAW or throw back QW. I think that he will take dumping the Q alone as a telegraph and play something pretty defensive. That said, my play of TRANQ almost certainly tells him that I have the otehr blank in hand. MAW looks alright with a pretty good tile pool, but this is still a really hard choice. I figured with TRAnQ that I'd have time to turn the other blank into a bingo.
>Brian_Bowman: AEFIORS 14D FARI.OSE +64 287
>jd: ?EEMSWZ 15A MEZE +54 310
>Brian_Bowman: EMOPR 15K MOPER +34 321
>jd: ?ANOOSW B2 WOO +18 328
#note it doesn't sim well, but I stand by this decision. Brian should really know that I have the blank. his next play is almost sure to block column B and/or row 12. I think that I really need lanes at this point in order to maximize my chances of winning. Here he can play at column A, but at the expense of leaving the bottom of the board wide open. meanwhile, until the plays at the top-left I have a lane for bingos starting with a P. not a guaranteed thing, certainly, but with a very favorable tile pool, also not an impossibility. the win percentages don't mean much because the board is tight and it is unclear unless I start opening spots that I will have somewhere to cash my blank.

quackle's favorite plays include WOO at F2, OW at 1A and WO at 14N. It's true that there's not many vowels left, so holding onto that O may be important. that said, I think I stand by this play.
>Brian_Bowman: HW 13G H.W +35 356
